        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(memory): keep ignored-name QMD roots watchable",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- keep explicitly configured QMD collection roots watchable when their directory name is normally ignored (`build`, `dist`, `vendor`, `.cache`)\n- prefer the most-specific configured QMD watch root before applying ignored-segment checks, so nested explicit roots are not shadowed by broader workspace roots\n- make QMD watcher ignore checks separator-aware so descendants like `<root>/..notes/daily.md` are treated as inside the configured root\n- isolate the deadcode pnpm fallback test from CI-managed `PATH` state\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts test/scripts/check-deadcode-unused-files.test.ts` (13 tooling + 126 memory-extension tests passed)\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs run --config test/vitest/vitest.full-core-support-boundary.config.ts` (3229 passed, 15 skipped)\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxlint extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.ts test/scripts/check-deadcode-unused-files.test.ts`\n- `node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.test.ts extensions/memory-core/src/memory/qmd-manager.ts test/scripts/check-deadcode-unused-files.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check origin/main...HEAD`\n- `node scripts/check-changed.mjs --dry-run`\n",
